Package ohos.light.bean

Class LightEffect

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.light.bean.LightEffect

  • public class LightEffect
extends Object
    Defines the blinking effects of lights.

    The blinking effects of a light include its brightness, lighting-on time, and lighting-off time.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Sensors#MISC_DEVICE

    • Constructor Detail

      • LightEffect

        public LightEffect​(LightBrightness lightBrightness,
                   int onDuration,
                   int offDuration)
        A constructor used to create a LightEffect instance.

        The instance can be used to pass a value to the LightEffect parameter in the LightAgent.turnOn(int, LightEffect) method to customize the blinking effect of the light.

        Parameters:
        lightBrightness - Indicates the customized brightness value of the light. LightBrightness specifies the available brightness values of three color channels.
        onDuration - Indicates the lighting-on time of a light during its one-shot blink, in milliseconds. The value range is 0-600000 ms, indicating that the lighting-on time of the light during its one-shot blink cannot exceed 10 minutes. When the parameter value is 0, the light is steady off. This parameter is invalid when it is set to a too large value or a negative value. Note that the actual lighting-on time is determined by the light itself.
        offDuration - Indicates the lighting-off time of the light, in milliseconds. The value range is 0-600000 ms, indicating that the lighting-off time of the light during its one-shot blink cannot exceed 10 minutes. When the parameter value is 0, the light is steady on. This parameter is invalid when it is set to a too large value or a negative value.
        Since:
        1
